word_mean_info__list.difference: 指在需要时可以动用的财产，包括国家土地、矿藏、水力等自然资源或个人的存款及其他财产。

含义较estate宽，指个人或团体合法拥有的财产，包括动产与不动产，或临时的财产。
多指地产或建在地面上的房产。

bilingual.source: He owns a piece of private property.
They decided to divide up the property.

bilingual.target: 请勿擅自进入私人财产。
私有财产受到法律保护。

bilingual.source: He inherited a large amount of property.

bilingual.target: 这栋房子是他的私人财产。

bilingual.source: The dog is trained to guard the property.
bilingual.target: 这条狗被训练来守护财产。

bilingual.source: She has a vested right to the property.
bilingual.target: 她对这处财产有既得的权利。

list.abstract: property（英[ˈprɒpəti]，美[ˈprɑːpərti]），英语单词。词性是名词，释义为个人财产；资产；所有物。例句：Their aim is to protect intellectual property.（他们的目标是保护知识产权。） 近义词为performance、nature、ownership。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey. Stop. That's company property.
yingyinNormal.zh: 给我住手！那是我公司的财产！

yingyinNormal.en: They're not your property. They were my friends.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们不是你的财产！他们是我的朋友。

yingyinNormal.en: I feel we must settle the question of who is to manage the baby's property.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得我们得定下来由谁来打理孩子的财产。

yingyinNormal.en: We can no longer afford to consider air and water common property free to be abused by anyone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们不得不考虑空气和水源，这些公共财产正被破坏。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Chairman, this invoice proves that Kalinda Sharma was engaged directly by the client, and therefore her notes are our client property.
yingyinNormal.zh: 主席先生，这张发票证明凯琳达·夏尔马由委托人直接雇用，因此她的记录是我委托人的财产。

yingyinNormal.en: Bailment describes a relationship in common law where a physical possession of personal property, or chattels, is transferred from one person, the bailor, to another person, the bailee.
yingyinNormal.zh: ‘委托’在普通法里的解释是当个人的私有财产，或者说动产，从委托人一方转移到受托人一方。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't want to. Not that my disinclination to discuss the topic should be interpreted as evidence of Howard Wolowitz's culpability in the destruction of government property worth millions of dollars.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不想谈，但是我不愿意谈这件事并不能证明是霍华德·沃罗威茨损坏了上千万美元的政府财产。

yingyinNormal.en: Like, well, I got rid of a couple husbands, now I'm gonna get rid of a mortgage, some maintenance, the tchotchskes, the homeowner's insurance, the property tax, the plumbing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 比如我摆脱掉了好几个丈夫，现在我马上又可以摆脱房贷赡养费，和一些细枝末节的费用房屋保险，财产税，管道维护费。

yingyinNormal.en: The biggest casualty to Faith was not life or property, however, but rather President Underwood's controversial America Works plan, which Congress defunded in order to free up resources for storm-related disaster relief.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而飓风费斯造成的最大损失不是财产人员损失，而是安德伍德总统大力推动却饱受争议的美国就业计划。因为国会撤回了资金以供应对飓风救灾之用。

yingyinNormal.en: He tracked them to this property in Argentina.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在追踪过程中，他发现了他们在阿根廷的房产。

yingyinNormal.en: One daughter, the heiress of Rosings and very extensive property.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她只有一个女儿，也就是罗新斯的继承人，将来可以继承到非常大的一笔遗产呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, he can be lost on someone else's property. Can't you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 他完全可以在别人的领地里迷路，不是吗？

yingyinNormal.en: It isn't even your pocket. Is it, son? Property of A.L. Ryerson.
yingyinNormal.zh: 连外套都是偷来的，它属于"AL莱尔森"。

yingyinNormal.en: Our interest in this place is entirely in the intellectual property. The code.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们对这个地方唯一的兴趣就是知识产权，就是代码。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, I have a question. How come it says Property of Human Services on his butt?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我有个问题耶，他的小屁股上为什么会有“失物招领”这些字？

yingyinNormal.en: No,no,no, I meant you don't belong here. I mean, in this room. This is my room. Property of Crane.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不不不，我的意思是这房间，你不该在这儿，这儿是我房间，鹤的私房。

yingyinNormal.en: Lily white. In your designer heels and tailored dresses, I mean, look at this property, Mrs. Underwood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 白得彻头彻尾，穿着设计师鞋，量体剪裁的衣服，看看这片地产，安德伍德夫人。

yingyinNormal.en: But when the property was coke, people stole the coke from somebody else not knowing who they took it from.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但当所有物只是可乐的时候，人们会从他人那儿把可乐偷走，即使不知道他们是从谁那儿偷走的。

yingyinNormal.en: These were not common refrigerator in the sense, everything belongs to everybody, everybody had their own property.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这不是个一般的公用冰箱，里面的东西并不属于每一个人，每个人都有自己的所有物。

yingyinNormal.en: Can I see that? Oh, of course. I'll get that back. Like all my underwear, that notebook says "Property of Sheldon Cooper."
yingyinNormal.zh: 我能看看吗？当然。我会拿回来的。就像我所有内裤，那个本子上也写着"所有权归谢尔顿·库珀"。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2018-2021年全国重点省市中考试卷，包括听力、阅读、完形、单选、填空、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a thing or things that are owned by someone; a possession or possessions
sense_info_list.zh: 财产; 资产; 所有物

examination_example.sentence: Some enemies decided to cheat them out of their <highlight>property</highlight> (财产) by making them quarrel about it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些敌人决定骗取他们的财产，让他们为之争吵。

examination_example.sentence: Others think that if rules are obeyed, there should be little risk to people and <highlight>property</highlight> (财产).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一些人认为，如果遵守规则，人和财产应该不会有什么风险。

examination_example.sentence: To Americans, pets are not just <highlight>property</highlight> (财产), but a part of the family.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对美国人来说，宠物不仅是财产，也是家庭的一部分。
